# Environment Variables for Vercel Deployment

## Required Environment Variables

Add these to your Vercel project settings:

### Firebase Service Account
```
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=zillion-builders-group
FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY_ID=your_private_key_id_here
FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYOUR_PRIVATE_KEY_HERE\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"
FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=firebase-adminsdk-xxxxx@zillion-builders-group.iam.gserviceaccount.com
FIREBASE_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here
FIREBASE_CLIENT_CERT_URL=https://www.googleapis.com/robot/v1/metadata/x509/firebase-adminsdk-xxxxx%40zillion-builders-group.iam.gserviceaccount.com
```

## How to Get These Values

1. Go to Firebase Console → Project Settings → Service Accounts
2. Click "Generate New Private Key"
3. Download the JSON file
4. Extract the values and add them to Vercel environment variables

## Important Notes

- The FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY should include the full key with \n characters
- Make sure all environment variables are set in Vercel project settings
- The API will automatically use these in production

## Local Development

For local development, the system will use the serviceAccountkey.json file.
For production, it will use the environment variables.
